adams.flow.control.Flow
	-annotation
	For each of the class label subsets (setosa, versicolor, virginica),\nthe following statistics are calculated for each of the attributes:\n  min, max, mean, stdev\nThe aggregates are computed in two ways:\n  1. using the SpreadSheetAggregate transformer\n  2. using the SpreadSheetQuery transformer using an SQL-like query language\nThe resulting spreadsheets are then displayed.
	-actor
		adams.flow.source.FileSupplier
			-file
			${EXAMPLE_FLOWS}/data/iris.csv
	-actor
		adams.flow.transformer.SpreadSheetFileReader
			-reader
				adams.data.io.input.CsvSpreadSheetReader
					-data-row-type
						adams.data.spreadsheet.DenseDataRow
					-spreadsheet-type
						adams.data.spreadsheet.SpreadSheet
					-missing
					
	-actor
		adams.flow.control.Branch
			-branch
				adams.flow.control.Sequence
					-name
					aggregates
					-actor
						adams.flow.transformer.SpreadSheetAggregate
							-key-columns
							last
							-aggregate-columns
							first
							-aggregate
							MIN
							-aggregate
							MAX
							-aggregate
							AVERAGE
							-aggregate
							STDEV
					-actor
						adams.flow.sink.SpreadSheetDisplay
							-name
							SpreadSheetDisplay (aggregates)
							-short-title
							true
							-writer
								adams.data.io.output.NullWriter
			-branch
				adams.flow.control.Sequence
					-name
					query
					-actor
						adams.flow.transformer.SpreadSheetQuery
							-query
							SELECT \n  MIN(sepallength) AS sl_min, \n  MAX(sepallength) AS sl_max, \n  AVERAGE(sepallength) AS sl_avg,\n  STDEV(sepallength) AS sl_stdev\nGROUP BY class
					-actor
						adams.flow.sink.SpreadSheetDisplay
							-name
							SpreadSheetDisplay (query)
							-short-title
							true
							-x
							-3
							-writer
								adams.data.io.output.NullWriter
	-flow-execution-listener
		adams.flow.execution.NullListener

